HEADWORD: Mistrustful
<hw>Mis*trust"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having or
causing mistrust, suspicions, or forebodings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their light blown out in some <qex>mistrustful</qex> wood.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mis*trust"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mis*trust"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mistrustingly</ent>⟦br⟧
